Business Brief -- PNC Financial Corp.:
   Pittsburgh Firm Will Buy
   Jenkintown, Pa., Concern
Under the agreement, PNC will pay Flagship shareholders
$13.05 a share, and PNC has also been granted an option to
buy as much as 19.99% of Flagship's common. Flagship's share
price jumped $2.375, to $11.875, in over-the-counter trading.
In late trading on the New York Stock Exchange, PNC was
quoted at $47.50, down 50 cents.
   For the first nine months of last year, Flagship had a
loss of $1.7 million, or 49 cents a share.